{
  "q1_accurate": [
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "note": "affected_via_composition gave the complete 52-holder list of `srv *Server` retainers with exact file:line (nomad/acl_endpoint.go:65, nomad/worker.go:92, nomad/job_endpoint_hooks.go:617, nomad/job_endpoint_validators.go:12, etc.) — I transcribed those refs directly into Step 4 section A without opening any of those files"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "note": "retained_via_interfaces was the core of the ticket: it named drainer.NodeDrainer via RaftApplier, volumewatcher.Watcher/volumeWatcher via CSIVolumeRPC, the three schedulers + PlanBuilder via Planner, auth.Authenticator via Encrypter, PeriodicDispatch via JobEvalDispatcher, and the client-side RPCer holders — each with carrier and chain"},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "nomad.Server", "note": "composed_by/includes pinned the embedded holders rpcHandler nomad/rpc.go:47, planner nomad/plan_apply.go:24, nodeHeartbeater nomad/heartbeat.go:37, and the struct span nomad/server.go:116-332"},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "nomad.NewServer (callees)", "note": "gave the whole construction contract in one call — setupRPC:1203, setupRaft:1345, setupSerf:1738, setupWorkers:1930, setupDeploymentWatcher:1156, setupVolumeWatcher:1178, setupNodeDrainer:1187, monitorLeadership nomad/leader.go:111, Shutdown:744 — all cited verbatim in Step 2"},
    {"tool": "sense_search", "query": "Nomad server construction and lifecycle", "note": "top hit agent.Agent.Server command/agent/agent.go:1566 plus nomad/server.go methods oriented me to the right package in one call"}
  ],
  "q1_wrong": [
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "nomad.NewServer (callees)", "note": "returned verify_hint 'Zero callers found in the index' for a function that is plainly called from command/agent/agent.go:1174 — contradicted by the same session's sense_blast, which listed agent.Agent.setupServer as an indirect caller via nomad.NewServer at hops 2"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "note": "retained_via_interfaces omitted the entire deploymentwatcher route (Watcher.raft/deploymentRPC/jobRPC, AllocUpdateBatcher.raft, deploymentWatcher.deploymentTriggers) — the single highest-risk holder set in the audit, and the only one that retains the server as a captured bound method (deploymentWatcherRaftShim.apply). It also omitted Variables.timers via variableTimers, despite sense_graph's `inherits` list naming nomad.variableTimers at nomad/variables_endpoint.go:39"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "note": "mixed test holders into the production list without flagging them (nomad.testcluster @ operator_endpoint_test.go:228, nomad.tlsTestHelper @ rpc_test.go:1363, mockJobEvalDispatcher, NoopScheduler) — I had to filter by filename by hand for a 'production code, not tests' ticket"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "note": "listed the client-side RPCer holders (allocrunner, csiHook, widmgr.Signer, allocwatcher) with chain 'agent.Agent > nomad.Server' as if live; grep showed config.RPCHandler is never assigned outside client/*_test.go, so that whole branch is inert in CE production — the chain field asserted a route that does not exist at runtime"}
  ],
  "q2_fallbacks": [
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "no deploymentwatcher rows at all; I grepped 'raft |deploymentRPC |jobRPC ' over nomad/deploymentwatcher/*.go and 'deploymentWatcherRaftShim' over nomad/*.go to recover DeploymentRaftEndpoints @ deployments_watcher.go:39/:76, batcher.go:20, deployment_watcher.go:65,:69,:73 and the shim at deployment_watcher_shims.go:13"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "fallback": "read", "missing": "rows gave holder + via + chain but no line for the retaining field itself in several cases; I read nomad/drainer/drainer.go for 'raft RaftApplier' (:159), nomad/volumewatcher/volume_watcher.go for 'rpc CSIVolumeRPC' (:30), client/allocwatcher/alloc_watcher.go for RPC/rpc (:66,:306), client/config/arconfig.go for RPCClient (:103)"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "no runtime-reachability signal on the client RPCer branch; I ran grep -rn 'RPCHandler' --include=*.go to establish it is test-only wiring, which downgraded 8 holders to Tier 4"},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "nomad.Server", "fallback": "read", "missing": "struct span nomad/server.go:116-332 but no field inventory; I sed-read :116-200 and :200-332 to enumerate the long-lived state (raft, fsm, deploymentWatcher:229, nodeDrainer:232, volumeWatcher:235, keyringReplicator:245, shutdownCtx:328) that Step 2 required"},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "nomad.NewServer (callees)", "fallback": "read", "missing": "callee list named setupNodeDrainer/setupDeploymentWatcher/setupVolumeWatcher but not the handover expressions inside them; I read nomad/server.go:1142-1205 to get 'raftShim := &deploymentWatcherRaftShim{apply: s.raftApply}' (:1160) and 'shim := drainerShim{s}' (:1190), which are the actual Step 3/Step 5 hops"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "fallback": "read", "missing": "Worker was listed as the Planner carrier but not the handover site; I grepped nomad/worker.go for NewScheduler to find :628 where `w` is passed as the planner"}
  ],
  "q3_hints": [
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query_before": "sense_blast nomad.Server (retained_via_interfaces rows carrying only holder/via/carrier/chain, plus retained_note saying 'blast a listed holder to go deeper')", "query_after": "grep -rn 'CSIVolumeRPC interface' -A 8 nomad/volumewatcher/ and 'RaftApplier interface' -A 10 nomad/drainer/", "hint": "retained_note: 'the holder declares a field typed as `via`; ... Which satisfier lands at runtime is unverified. Not counted in total_affected; blast a listed holder to go deeper.' — the explicit 'unverified' caveat told me the routes needed manual confirmation, so I went to grep for the interface definitions rather than blasting each holder"},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query_before": "sense_graph nomad.Server (completeness verdict 'complete', omitted_edges 123)", "query_after": "sense_blast nomad.Server with max_hops 3, issued in the same parallel block", "hint": "next_steps: '51 callers found — check blast radius before changing this symbol' — I had already paired the two calls, and the blast is what surfaced retained_via_interfaces, the section the ticket actually turned on"},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query_before": "sense_graph nomad.NewServer direction=callees", "query_after": "I did NOT re-run with min_confidence=0.3 as suggested; I moved to reading nomad/server.go:1142-1205 directly", "hint": "verify_hint 'Zero callers found in the index... Verify with: grep -rn NewServer .' plus next_steps 'min_confidence=0.3' — the hint was pointed at a false negative I already knew was false from the blast's indirect_callers, so it cost a moment of doubt rather than redirecting me usefully"}
  ],
  "q4_value": "retained_via_interfaces on sense_blast nomad.Server — one call named holders that never import the nomad package and never spell *Server: drainer.NodeDrainer behind RaftApplier, the three schedulers plus PlanBuilder behind sstructs.Planner, auth.Authenticator behind auth.Encrypter, volumewatcher behind CSIVolumeRPC, each with carrier and containment chain. That is exactly the 'easy-to-miss' class the ticket was about, and grep has no query for it — you cannot grep for 'field typed as a local interface that *Server happens to satisfy'. It converted an open-ended hunt into a verification pass.",
  "q5_improve": "Make retained_via_interfaces complete and production-aware. It missed the single highest-risk route in the audit (deploymentwatcher: Watcher.raft/deploymentRPC/jobRPC, AllocUpdateBatcher.raft, deploymentWatcher.deploymentTriggers) — almost certainly because deploymentWatcherRaftShim retains the server as a captured bound method value (apply: s.raftApply) rather than a struct field, and because DeploymentRPC/JobRPC are empty interfaces in CE. Bound-method-value capture and empty-interface satisfaction are precisely the cases with zero compile-time signal, so they are the ones a lifecycle audit most needs indexed. Alongside that: give each row the file:line of the retaining field itself (not just the holder's declaration), and mark rows whose chain has no production assignment site — the client RPCer rows were reported with chain 'agent.Agent > nomad.Server' when config.RPCHandler is only ever set in client/*_test.go.",
  "score": 8,
  "score_rationale": "Two calls (sense_blast + sense_graph on nomad.Server) produced ~75 of the 83 holders with citable file:line and surfaced the interface-mediated retainers I could not have enumerated with grep — but the omission of the entire deploymentwatcher route, the missing field-level lines for drainer/volumewatcher/allocwatcher, the unflagged test holders, and the false 'zero callers' on NewServer all forced grep/read fallbacks to finish, which is the 7-8 band rather than 9-10."
}

